qas.question: The English word Alps derives from what Latin Word?
Who says that all high mountains are called Alpes by Celts?
What languages have terms for high mountains derived from alp?

context: The English word Alps derives from the Latin <a0_0>Alpes<a0_0/> (through French). <a1_0>Maurus Servius Honoratus<a1_0/>, an ancient commentator of Virgil, says in his commentary (A. X 13) that all high mountains are called Alpes by Celts. The term may be common to Italo-Celtic, because the <a2_0>Celtic languages<a2_0/> have terms for high mountains derived from alp.
